edu.uiuc.ncsa.security.core.configuration.provider

Class MultiTypeProvider<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.uiuc.ncsa.security.core.configuration.provider.HierarchicalConfigProvider<T>
      • edu.uiuc.ncsa.security.core.configuration.provider.TypedProvider<T>
        • edu.uiuc.ncsa.security.core.configuration.provider.MultiTypeProvider<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CfgEventListener, EventListener, javax.inject.Provider<T>

    public abstract class MultiTypeProvider<T>
extends TypedProvider<T>
    A configured provider that notifies its listeners when its get method is called and returns the first non-null object. It no listeners respond, then this provides for a default store. Note that this should be the top-level provider for stores that can have multiple implementations. It's constructors are, by and large, ignored but need to be there for Apache's APIs.

    Created by Jeff Gaynor
    on 1/18/12 at 10:09 AM
